S6.T1.caption: Table 1: A summary of application domains tackled by VQA literature with a summary of the features of the datasets used as benchmarks. Also, the approaches are reported, with the best results for each dataset. Following a legend for interpret the table: Dataset: C:Classes, L:Labels. Dataset Size: AS: Audio Scenes, C:Classes, T:Text, HoV:Hours of Video, I:images, Ic:Icons, V:Videos. Notes: A:Answers, At:Attributes, C:Classes, Cap:Caption, I:Images, Imp:Impression, Q:Questions. Approaches: AM:Attention Mechanism, BM:Bert Model, CM:Classifier Model, DN:DenseNet, ED:Encoder-Decoder, F:Fusion, FRCNN: Faster-RCNN, GM:Generative Model, IA: Image Attention, IN:ImageNet, IV2: InceptionV2, MLA:MultiLevel Attention, MMFN:Multi-Step Modality Fusion Network, QCM:Question Classifier Model, RM:Reasoning Module, RN:ResNet, TE:Text Embedding, WE:Word Embedding,W2V:Word2Vec. Best Results: ACC:Accuracy, BLEU:Bilingual Evaluation Understudy Score: TDA:Task Dendendant Accuracy, WBSS:Word-Based Semantic Similarity
